article.headline: Detroit 68, Chicago St 65
article.story: DETROIT (AP) -- Brandon Cotton scored 18 points to lead Detroit to a 68-65 win over Chicago State on Monday night. Chicago State trailed by as many as 12 points in the first half. The last time came after two free throws by Cotton, which put the Titans (6-5) ahead 27-15 with 5:59 remaining. But the Cougars (1-8) took the lead with a 17-4 run that included all nine of Michael Henderson's first-half points. Detroit led 34-33 at halftime and increased its lead to as many as nine points before Chicago State mounted another comeback. Jon Goode's two free throws with 3:53 left put Detroit ahead 59-58, and the Titans retained the lead the rest of the way. Goode also made three of four shots from the line in the final 21 seconds. Torvoris Baker added a season-high 17 points for Detroit and grabbed a game-high eight rebounds. Royce Parran led the Cougars with 19 points, and Henderson finished with 13.
